				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">SoE owes us replacement songs<a name="60322"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 8:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> The final area nerf is scheduled for Sept 14.  This will make several of our songs completely useless unless you like killing mass amounts of greenies. Even if you weren't an area kiter there may have been times you used theses songs for agro reasons and CC. When they are changed to melee range there will probably be no real use for them...... So.
<br />

<br />
 Why not just completely remove them from the game and give us some useful songs in return.
<br />

<br />
 Some songs I would find useful :
<br />

<br />
 A snare that only snares so it is less likely to be resisted. How about a one minute duration? Yea thats probaly to much to ask.
<br />

<br />
 A regen song that only Regens HP's. It would be mainly useful soloing. Give it a base of 30 hp per tick thats 50% more than the Marr songs
<br />
 
<br />
 A debuff song that debuffs all resists unlike HoS that does M,F,C only.
<br />

<br />
 I'm assuming Druids and Wizards will still be able to quad kite. Well then remove or drastically decrease the mana cost on DDD then we will have a quad song too.
<br />

<br />
 I'm tired of hearing SoE say &quot;it wasn't our intention when we made these songs&quot;. Could you at least say what your intention was?
<br />
  </span></td>
