				<td colspan="2"><span>Wizard/druid quad kiting has serious disadvantages over AEing. For one, they need to med for very long periods of time after a kite, because even at 60+ mana/tick it takes a long time to regen thousands of mana. Fairly good gear is required, otherwise your mana will hit zero before you kill all the mobs, whereas you really just need a TDoK for AEing. Also, AE potential is much greater than quad potential. I think it was Worry that killed every kitable HoH mob in 20 minutes solo for like 6AA. As far as PoFire/Tipt/etc soloing, that requires flagging and good gear also. I think a necro can make an AA in ~45 minutes in PoF, and of course this is an elemental+ necro. Any 65 bard can make an AA in a bit over an hour just swarming in PoN. 
<br />

<br />
You can't base your arguments on &quot;enchanters can get 3AA/hour in Tipt.&quot; SOE will fix (nerf) it eventually, they don't like it any more than they do AEing. It was never intended that any one character would be so effective, it's just very hard to stop players from &quot;exploiting&quot; game mechanics.</span></td>
