<br />

<br />
They want us as a class, but they don't like all the interesting things we can do.  Look at the last 4 expansions.  Where are the fun interesting songs?  Don't exist.  We got an huge upgrade in PoP, but since than everything has been related to PoP songs or to match other classes spells (loy cure songs, reflect).  OOW looks to be the same thing.  If you look at the new chanter/shammy spells they have crit/avoidance parts to them.  Where is this in ours?  All the hybird classes pretty much have spell procs to add to melee, we have what? A lvl 40 or something song who's effect doesn't stack with cripple.
<br />

<br />
It just seems like they have been and will continue to fit us in a box since PoP.  This makes us definable I guess, DS (slow cuts damage to nothing), haste (kinda), resists, mana (no one really needs anymore), ok debuffs, crappy dots, mezz/lull, and our ablity to pull.
<br />

<br />
Don't get me wrong still having a blast and love my bard, but don't like the fact that they are taking away what we can do and limiting our options. </span></td>
